  {
    "id": "48ef42d5-bff0-4253-a5cf-902c61c8fdce",
    "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Foreign_Marriage_Act,_1969",
    "title": "Foreign Marriage Act, 1969 (India)",
    "summary": "The Foreign Marriage Act, 1969 was enacted by the Parliament of India on 31 August 1969 following the Third Law Commission's recommendations to streamline the recognition of marriages solemnised abroad involving Indian citizens. Its primary purpose is to recognize marriages of Indian citizens performed outside India, including unions between an Indian and a foreign national. The Act has been subject to judicial scrutiny, notably in Supriyo v. Union of India, where petitioners sought to strike down notice and objection provisions as violative of fundamental rights under Articles 14, 15, 19 and 21 of the Constitution. The Supreme Court is hearing challenges that also encompass parallel provisions in the Special Marriage Act, 1954, aiming to protect vulnerable minorities.",
