    "source": "https://www.livelaw.in/top-stories/marriage-considered-pious-in-indian-society-divorce-on-ground-of-irretrievable-breakdown-of-marriage-not-always-desirable-supreme-court-239856",
    "title": "Supreme Court: Marriage is pious; divorce on irretrievable breakdown not always desirable",
    "summary": "The Supreme Court reiterated that marriage is a sacred institution in Indian society and cautioned against treating divorce on the ground of irretrievable breakdown as a routine remedy. While recognising genuine breakdown, the Court emphasized the need to balance individual rights with societal interest in preserving marriage. It directed courts to exercise discretion, consider alternatives such as reconciliation, and ensure that divorce does not become a preferred recourse. The judgment underscores the importance of the constitutional right to life and liberty under Article 21 while upholding family values.",
