    "sections": [
      {
        "title": "Judgment Overview",
        "content": "The Court examined the growing trend of granting divorce on the ground of irretrievable breakdown and stressed that marriage, being a pious social contract, must not be hastily terminated."
      },
      {
        "title": "Legal Reasoning",
        "content": "Balancing the right to personal liberty under Article 21 with the social objective of preserving family, the Court held that courts should assess each case meticulously, encouraging reconciliation where possible."
      },
      {
        "title": "Implications for Family Courts",
        "content": "Family courts are directed to apply a discretionary approach, consider counselling, and ensure that divorce is not treated as a default remedy, thereby reinforcing the protective ethos of the Hindu Marriage Act."
      }
