    "id": "5e01dd9f-95b4-4093-8a53-71e8c07dc17e",
    "source": "https://www.livelaw.in/top-stories/maintenance-orders-not-to-be-stayed-unless-for-very-special-reasons-148451",
    "title": "Supreme Court Bars Stays on Section 125 Maintenance Orders Except for Very Special Reasons",
    "summary": "The Supreme Court has ruled that orders for maintenance under Section 125 of the Criminal Procedure Code cannot be stayed by appellate courts unless the applicant satisfies the stringent test of \"very special reasons.\" The judgment emphasises the paramount importance of safeguarding the rights of women and children who depend on these orders for livelihood. While the Court recognised limited exceptions—such as evident abuse of process or manifest injustice—it cautioned lower courts against frivolous or routine stays. The decision is expected to streamline enforcement of maintenance orders and reduce procedural delays that often jeopardise the welfare of dependents.",
