    "title": "Ancestral Property and Coparcenary under the Succession Act – Mitakshara Perspective",
    "summary": "The article analyses the application of the Indian Succession Act to ancestral property governed by the Mitakshara school of Hindu law. It examines the doctrine of coparcenary, the rights of male and female members, and the impact of the Hindu Succession (Amendment) Act, 2005 on share entitlement. The discussion highlights procedural aspects of partition, survivorship, and the role of testamentary disposition within a Mitakshara coparcenary. Recent judicial pronouncements interpreting Section 6 and Section 8 of the Succession Act are also reviewed.",
