  {
    "id": "34f781dd-988f-42b8-9b59-62e693899095",
    "source": "http://indiankanoon.org:80/doc/100/",
    "title": "Sakaldeep Manjhi vs State of Bihar – Bail Order dated 7 July 2008",
    "summary": "The petitioner, Sakaldeep Manjhi, was found in possession of a country‑made pistol and ammunition while police were searching for an accused in another matter. The Patna High Court, after considering the circumstances, refused to order his release from custody and dismissed the petition. The Court directed that the petitioner would be released after completing one year of custody in Nagarnausa Police Station case No. 12 of 2008, subject to furnishing a bond satisfactory to the judicial magistrate. The order was pronounced by Justice Dharnidhar Jha, with implementation to be overseen by Judicial Magistrate P.C. Pandey, Ist Class, Hilsa, Nalanda.",
    "law_type": "family_law",
    "entities": [
      {
        "type": "person",
