        "title": "Background and Issue",
        "content": "The petition sought a divorce decree under mutual consent despite the statutory six‑month separation period not being completed."
      },
      {
        "title": "Supreme Court’s Observation on Article 142",
        "content": "The Court held that its power under Article 142 to do complete justice allows it to grant a decree when parties have settled and there is no opposition."
      },
      {
        "title": "Interpretation of Section 13(b)",
        "content": "While the statutory requirement of a cooling‑off period remains, the Court clarified that it can issue a decree in exceptional cases without contravening the Act."
