    "source": "https://www.livelaw.in/top-stories/marriage-between-muslim-man-and-a-hindu-woman-142316?utm_partner=livelaw",
    "title": "Supreme Court rules child of Muslim‑Hindu fasid marriage entitled to father's property",
    "summary": "The Supreme Court of India held that a child born out of a marriage between a Muslim man and his Hindu wife is a legitimate heir and may claim a share in the father's property. The Court clarified that such a marriage is neither valid (sahih) nor void (batil) under Muslim personal law but is an irregular (fasid) marriage, which does not invalidate the legitimacy of offspring. Consequently, only children born out of a void (batil) marriage or outside any marriage are considered illegitimate. The judgment upheld a Kerala High Court decision confirming the child's right to inheritance.",
