  {
    "id": "6e82f4a4-146a-4907-8051-f3a159a9683e",
    "source": "https://www.livelaw.in/top-stories/marriage-equality-case-justice-sanjiv-khanna-recuses-from-hearing-review-petitions-in-supreme-court-262920",
    "title": "Justice Sanjiv Khanna Recuses from Supreme Court Review of Same‑Sex Marriage Verdict",
    "summary": "On 10 July 2024 the Supreme Court postponed the hearing of review petitions challenging its 17 October 2023 judgment that declined to recognize same‑sex marriages, after Justice Sanjiv Khanna recused himself from the bench. The original five‑judge bench, which included Justices Sanjay Kishan Kaul and S. Ravindra Bhat, was reconstituted with Justices Sanjiv Khanna and B.V. Nagarathna replacing the retired judges, alongside CJI D.Y. Chandrachud, Justice Hima Kohli and Justice P.S. Narasimha. The Court had affirmed that queer couples have a right to cohabit without violence but stopped short of granting legal recognition as marriage, directing the Union of India to set up a committee to examine rights of queer unions. Review petitioners argue that the judgment violates fundamental rights and contains errors apparent on the face of the record. A new bench will have to be formed before the review petitions can be heard.",
    "law_type": "family_law",
    "entities": [
      {
        "type": "court",
        "name": "Supreme Court of India"
      },
      {
        "type": "person",
        "name": "Justice Sanjiv Khanna"
      },
      {
        "type": "person",
        "name": "Chief Justice of India D.Y. Chandrachud"
      },
      {
        "type": "person",
        "name": "Justice B.V. Nagarathna"
      },
      {
        "type": "person",
        "name": "Justice Sanjay Kishan Kaul"
      },
      {
        "type": "person",
        "name": "Justice S. Ravindra Bhat"
      },
      {
        "type": "person",
        "name": "Justice Hima Kohli"
      },
      {
        "type": "person",
        "name": "Justice P.S. Narasimha"
      },
      {
        "type": "case",
        "name": "Supriyo @ Supriya Chakraborty v. Union of India (RP (c) 1866/2023)"
      },
      {
        "type": "concept",
        "name": "same‑sex marriage"
      },
      {
        "type": "concept",
        "name": "civil union"
      },
      {
        "type": "concept",
        "name": "fundamental rights"
      },
      {
        "type": "concept",
        "name": "discrimination"
      }
    ],
    "sections": [
      {
        "title": "Background Judgment (17 Oct 2023)",
        "content": "The Supreme Court declined to legally recognise same‑sex marriages, holding that the issue is for the legislature, but affirmed the right of queer couples to cohabit without violence and directed the Union to constitute a committee to examine rights of queer unions."
      },
      {
        "title": "Recusal and Bench Reconstitution",
        "content": "Following the retirements of Justices Kaul and Bhat, Justices Sanjiv Khanna and B.V. Nagarathna were appointed to the five‑judge bench. Justice Khanna recused himself from the review petitions, necessitating the formation of a new bench before further proceedings."
      },
      {
        "title": "Review Petitions and Procedural Orders",
        "content": "Petitioners sought an open‑court hearing of the review petitions. The CJI reiterated that review petitions are traditionally heard in chambers. The Court ordered the review petitions to be circulated to a bench that does not include Justice Khanna."
      },
      {
        "title": "Key Legal Issues Raised",
        "content": "The petitioners contend that the original judgment violates fundamental rights by failing to provide legal protection to queer couples, alleging errors apparent on the face of the record, self‑contradiction, and manifest injustice."
      }
    ],
