  {
    "id": "f4916ae2-9aa0-4d83-b4b7-2b3a708399c1",
    "source": "https://www.livelaw.in/top-stories/marriage-equality-case-justice-sanjiv-khanna-recuses-from-hearing-review-petitions-in-supreme-court-262920?trk=article-ssr-frontend-pulse_little-text-block",
    "title": "Justice Sanjiv Khanna Recuses from Review of Same‑Sex Marriage Verdict in Supreme Court",
    "summary": "On 10 July 2024 Justice Sanjiv Khanna withdrew from a newly constituted bench hearing review petitions challenging the Supreme Court’s October 2023 decision that declined to recognise same‑sex marriages. The recusal necessitates the formation of another bench before the Court can proceed with the petitions. The original judgment held that legal recognition of queer unions is a legislative matter, though it directed the Union of India to set up a committee to examine rights of persons in queer unions and affirmed the right of queer couples to cohabit without interference. Petitioners argue the judgment leaves a gap in protection of fundamental rights and contains errors apparent on the face of the record. The Chief Justice indicated that review petitions are ordinarily heard in chambers, not in open court.",
