    ],
    "sections": [
      {
        "title": "Recusal of Justice Sanjiv Khanna",
        "content": "Justice Sanjiv Khanna withdrew from the bench hearing the review petitions, prompting the Court to reconstitute the bench before proceeding."
      },
      {
        "title": "Composition of the New Bench",
        "content": "The bench now includes CJI D.Y. Chandrachud, Justice Hima Kohli, Justice P.S. Narasimha, Justice B.V. Nagarathna, with the two retired judges (Justices Kaul and Bhat) replaced."
      },
      {
        "title": "Procedural Direction on Review Petitions",
        "content": "The Court ordered that the review petitions be circulated to a bench that does not include Justice Khanna and that the Registry follow administrative instructions for appropriate bench allocation."
      },
      {
        "title": "Supreme Court’s October 2023 Judgment on Queer Unions",
        "content": "The Court declined to recognise same‑sex marriage, stating it is for the legislature, while directing the Union to set up a committee to study rights of queer unions and affirming the right to cohabit without violence."
      },
      {
        "title": "Petitioners’ Grounds for Review",
        "content": "Petitioners contend the judgment fails to protect queer couples’ fundamental rights, contains apparent errors, is self‑contradictory, and amounts to judicial abdication."
      }
