  {
    "id": "60282610-1228-4e04-a85e-e6f34c612410",
    "source": "https://www.livelaw.in/top-stories/marriage-equality-case-new-bench-of-supreme-court-to-consider-review-petitions-on-january-9-280230",
    "title": "Supreme Court Constitutes New Bench to Hear Review Petitions in Marriage Equality Case",
    "summary": "The Supreme Court of India has formed a new five‑judge bench to consider review petitions challenging its October 2023 verdict that declined to legally recognize queer marriages. The bench, comprising Justices B.R. Gavai, Surya Kant, B.V. Nagarathna, P.S. Narasimha and Dipankar Datta, will hear the petitions in chambers on January 9. The original judgment held that marriage recognition is a legislative matter, although it acknowledged the right of queer couples to cohabit without violence and called for a governmental committee to study their rights. Review petitions argue that the judgment violates fundamental rights by failing to prohibit discrimination against queer couples. The hearing follows the recusal of Justice Sanjiv Khanna and the retirement of several original bench members.",
    "law_type": "family_law",
    "entities": [
      {
        "type": "court",
        "name": "Supreme Court of India"
      },
      {
        "type": "person",
        "name": "Justice B.R. Gavai"
      },
      {
