    "source": "https://www.livelaw.in/top-stories/marriage-equality-case-supreme-court-to-consider-review-petitions-on-july-10-justices-sanjiv-khanna-nagarathna-replace-retired-judges-262387",
    "title": "Supreme Court to Hear Review Petitions on Same‑Sex Marriage Recognition on July 10, 2024",
    "summary": "On July 10, 2024 the Supreme Court will list review petitions challenging its October 17, 2023 judgment that declined to legally recognise same‑sex marriages, holding that the matter rests with Parliament. A new bench composition will hear the matter, with retired Justices Sanjay Kishan Kaul and S. Ravindra Bhat replaced by Justices Sanjiv Khanna and B.V. Nagarathna alongside CJI D.Y. Chandrachud, Justice Hima Kohli and Justice P.S. Narasimha. The original judgment affirmed the right of queer couples to cohabit without violence but stopped short of ordering civil unions or marriage recognition, prompting petitions alleging fundamental‑rights violations and errors apparent on the face of the record. The petitions argue that the Court has abdicated its duty to protect LGBTQ rights and seek a directive for legislative action or judicially enforceable protections. The outcome will shape the future of marriage equality and LGBTQ rights in India.",
