    "title": "Supreme Court to Hear Review Petitions on Same‑Sex Marriage Recognition on July 10, 2024",
    "summary": "The Supreme Court of India listed review petitions challenging its October 17, 2023 judgment that declined to accord legal recognition to same‑sex marriages. The review will be heard by a reconstituted five‑judge bench after the retirements of Justices Sanjay Kishan Kaul and S. Ravindra Bhat, with Justices Sanjiv Khanna and B.V. Nagarathna joining Chief Justice D.Y. Chandrachud, Justice Hima Kohli and Justice P.S. Narasimha. While the original judgment directed the Union of India to set up a committee to study the rights and entitlements of queer unions, it stopped short of mandating any statutory definition of marriage or civil union. The petitioners argue that the judgment leaves queer couples without essential legal protection, alleging errors apparent on the face of the record. The forthcoming hearing will determine whether the Court will expand its protective jurisprudence or defer the issue entirely to Parliament.",
