    "source": "https://taxguru.in/income-tax/tax-incentives-fdi-effective-era-global-minimum-tax.html",
    "title": "Assessing the Effectiveness of Tax Incentives for Foreign Direct Investment in the Global Minimum Tax Era",
    "summary": "The article examines how tax incentives such as holidays, credits, and preferential rates are used by governments to attract foreign direct investment (FDI) and analyses their efficiency, equity, and neutrality. It argues that many incentives are redundant, offering little incremental investment while causing fiscal leakage and undermining public spending. The piece highlights equity concerns where large multinational enterprises receive preferential treatment compared to domestic SMEs, potentially fostering enclave economies and round‑tripping. Finally, it discusses how these incentives disturb market neutrality, distorting capital allocation and conflicting with emerging international standards like the global minimum tax.",
