      {
        "title": "I. Introduction",
        "content": "Overview of the global competition for FDI and the role of tax incentives such as holidays, credits, accelerated depreciation, and SEZ rates."
      },
      {
        "title": "II. Efficiency and the Problem of Fiscal Redundancy",
        "content": "Analysis of whether incentives generate incremental investment and the fiscal leakage caused by redundant measures."
      },
      {
        "title": "III. The Equity Dilemma: Favoured MNEs vs. Local Enterprises",
        "content": "Discussion of how tax incentives create a tiered tax burden, fostering enclave economies and round‑tripping."
      },
