    "source": "https://taxguru.in/corporate-law/arrest-illegal-written-grounds-supplied-remand-supreme-court.html",
    "title": "Supreme Court Holds Arrest Illegal Without Written Grounds Supplied Before Remand",
    "summary": "The Supreme Court examined the constitutional mandate under Article 22(1) of the Constitution and Section 47 of the Bharatiya Nagarik Suraksha Sanhita, 2023, requiring that an arrestee be furnished the grounds of arrest in writing. While oral communication is permissible in exigent circumstances, the Court stipulated that written grounds must be supplied in a language understood by the arrestee at least two hours before the arrestee is produced before the magistrate for remand. Failure to meet this timeline renders both the arrest and subsequent remand illegal, entitling the person to release. The judgment also reinforced the duty to inform relatives or nominated persons under Section 48 of the BNSS 2023 and clarified that the procedural safeguard applies to all offences. The appeals were dismissed and interim bail in related matters was ordered to continue.",
